Task 1: Digital Literacy Visual Resource
For this task, I designed a one-page infographic using Canva. The design is tailored specifically for my batchmates at VIT Bhopal, aiming to simplify the broad concept of digital literacy into actionable steps. The visual resource is divided into three core segments: a modern definition of digital literacy, a curated list of essential tools like GitHub and Overleaf for CSE students, and a “Cyber-Safety” checklist to protect student identities online. I utilized a clean, tech-oriented color palette (VIT Blue and Slate Grey) to ensure the information is readable and professional.
One thing I found particularly interesting while creating this design was the challenge of “visual hierarchy.” As a CSE student, I am used to technical documentation, but translating complex security concepts into simple, catchy icons required a different type of “design thinking.” It was difficult to decide which tools to include, as the digital landscape is vast, but I prioritized tools that offer the most academic value. This process taught me that being a Digital Ambassador is as much about effective communication as it is about technical knowledge.

